      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 307: 🔴 Thread safety: `pushWakeLock` and `pushEventDisposable` are accessed from multiple threads (push handler threads call `onPushReceived()`, main looper runs `releasePushHold()`) without synchronization. The null-check-then-assign on `pushWakeLock` is a classic race condition that can lead to double-acquire or a leaked WakeLock.\n\nAdditionally, when a second push arrives while the WakeLock is already held, it is not re-acquired with a fresh timeout. If the first WakeLock\u0027s 35s timeout expires before the re-armed `pushMaxWindowMs` (25s from the second push) fires, the device may sleep during active processing.\n\n```suggestion\n        synchronized(this) {\n            val wl \u003d pushWakeLock\n            if (wl \u003d\u003d null) {\n                val pm \u003d getSystemService(POWER_SERVICE) as PowerManager\n                pushWakeLock \u003d pm.newWakeLock(PowerManager.PARTIAL_WAKE_LOCK, \"jami:push-app\").apply {\n                    setReferenceCounted(false)\n                    acquire(pushMaxWindowMs + 10_000L)\n                }\n            } else {\n                // Extend timeout for overlapping pushes\n                wl.acquire(pushMaxWindowMs + 10_000L)\n            }\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "23473aaa47b369e00f49887ab852367c183dd180",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
