      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 370: 🔴 Logic bug: `releasePushHold()` unconditionally disposes `pushEventDisposable` before checking `activePushCount`. When count \u003e 0 and the method defers by re-posting the runnable, the event subscription is already gone. This means for the deferred window, daemon events will NOT trigger early release — the system always falls back to the full `pushMaxWindowMs` timeout, defeating the purpose of event-driven release.\n\nMove the dispose after the count check:\n```suggestion\n    private fun releasePushHold() {\n        // If a new push came in while we were waiting, defer release.\n        if (activePushCount.get() \u003e 0) {\n            Log.d(TAG, \"Push: still ${activePushCount.get()} in flight, deferring release\")\n            pushReleaseHandler.postDelayed(pushReleaseRunnable, pushMaxWindowMs)\n            return\n        }\n\n        pushEventDisposable?.dispose()\n        pushEventDisposable \u003d null\n\n        try { pushWakeLock?.release() } catch (_: Exception) {}\n        pushWakeLock \u003d null\n```",
      "revId": "23473aaa47b369e00f49887ab852367c183dd180",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
